Neviot-Teva Stock Jumps by Most in Seven Years on Buyout Offer

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-10-10T08:48:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/neviot-teva-stock-jumps-by-most-in-seven-years-on-buyout-offer.html
Neviot-Teva Hagalil Ltd. soared the
most in more than seven years after controlling shareholder
Central Beverage Co.  offered  to buy the rest of the mineral-
water bottler for 12.907 shekels a share.  The shares surged 35 percent, the biggest intraday gain
since March 2004, to 10.61 shekels at 10:15 a.m. in  Tel Aviv ,
giving the Lod, Israel-based company a market value of 103
million shekels ($28 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  